external_knowledge:
- "voyagers" refers to users who have rated the movies;
- "navigating through the realm" refers to the act of rating movies;
- "Peter Jackson's cinematic universe" refers to movies directed by Peter Jackson;
- "celestial bodies" are metaphors for the titles of the movies;
- "cosmic shepherd" refers to the director of the movies, Peter Jackson.

sql:
SELECT username 
FROM users
WHERE user_id = (SELECT user_id FROM ratings WHERE rating = (SELECT MAX(rating) FROM ratings));

external_knowledge:
- "maestro" refers to the director;
- "cinematic creation" refers to the movies they have directed;
- "ascended to the pinnacle of audience appreciation" implies having the highest average rating;
- "starlight they've garnered" refers to the ratings given by the audience.

- 'prolific' refers to a director who has directed more than 10 films;
- 'average rating' is the mean value of all ratings given to the director's films;
- 'high average ratings' indicates sorting the results in descending order based on the average rating.
